Popular Agbeni market in Ibadan, Oyo State, has been razed down by fire. Consequently, goods and properties with millions of naira have been destroyed as a result of the inferno. It was gathered that the market gutted fire at about 04:30am, on Sunday. The cause of the fire could not yet be established as at the time of filing this report. The state General Manager of Fire Services, Yemi Akinyemi, confirmed the incident to our journalists when contacted. Akinyemi said, “The agency received the distress call at exactly 04:37hrs through Sunday Ogundele, Access Bank security that Agbeni market is on fire. “Our men are still battling with the job, we are grateful to Central Bank of Nigeria that allows us to use their water supply. Everything is under control. They are still going to CBN to replenish”, he confirmed.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ South West Zonal Director of the National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) Mr. Akiode when contacted told DAILY INDEPENDENT that personnel of the agency have been deployed to the scene and will provide more details in due time. POLL More details later…